reviewText: This investigation into the fate of Cleopatra's palace and library is a wonderful introduction to the topic. Since it was produced, however, the Egyptian government has constructed a remarkable new library near the site of the two thousand year old underwater ruins of the original. This film would could use an upgrade to include this new construction, added to the overall topic of her capital city, her palace and library, and their collective fates. This film is very good as far as it goes, nevertheless.
